Because `ker f = {r : R | f r = 0}`, so `x ∈ ker f` is `x ∈ {r : R | f r = 0}`, which is `f x = 0`.

Now, `Set.mem_setOf_eq` is `x ∈ {x | p x} ↔ p x`.

Thus, `Set.mem_setOf_eq` can rewrite `x ∈ {r : R | f r = 0}` as `f x = 0`.

Alternatively, `simp [mem_ker]` directly does the same thing, because `mem_ker` is `x ∈ ker f ↔ f x = 0`. 

